# Component Design Rules

## Philosophy

Components should be:

* reusable
* composable
* predictable
* easy to understand

Avoid giant components.

---

## Reusability

Extract reusable UI when:

* repeated more than twice
* improves readability
* encapsulates styling
* encapsulates logic

Do NOT create tiny wrapper components with no benefit.

---

## Component Structure

Preferred order:

Imports

Types

Constants

Component

Helper functions

Export

---

## Props

Prefer explicit props.

Avoid passing unnecessary props.

Use interfaces.

Example:

interface FeatureCardProps {
title: string;
description: string;
icon: ReactNode;
}

---

## Variants

When components have multiple styles,
use variants instead of duplication.

Good:

<Button variant="primary" />

<Button variant="secondary" />

Not:

PrimaryButton

SecondaryButton

DangerButton

---

## Lists

Never duplicate JSX.

Instead:

const features = [...]

features.map(...)

---

## Sections

Landing pages should be broken into sections.

Example:

Navbar

Hero

LogoCloud

Features

Pricing

Testimonials

FAQ

CTA

Footer

---

## Cards

Cards should accept props.

Avoid hardcoding content.

---

## Buttons

Reuse a common Button component.

Never duplicate button styling.

---

## Forms

Inputs should share:

* spacing
* typography
* borders
* focus styles
* validation styles

Use reusable form components.

---

## Containers

Use a reusable container pattern.

Example:

max-w-7xl

mx-auto

px-4

sm:px-6

lg:px-8

Avoid repeating layout classes everywhere.

---

## Section Spacing

Maintain consistent spacing.

Prefer:

py-12

py-16

py-20

Do not randomly mix spacing.

---

## Animations

Animations should be subtle.

Avoid distracting effects.

Prefer CSS transitions over JavaScript.

---

## Maintainability

Before adding a new component ask:

Can an existing component solve this?

If yes, extend it instead of creating another.

---

## Final Review

Every component should be:

✓ Reusable

✓ Typed

✓ Responsive

✓ Accessible

✓ Semantic

✓ Uses design tokens

✓ Uses Tailwind correctly

✓ Easy to read

✓ Easy to extend

✓ Production-ready
